ms in the post-nation-state era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aEurope.  aJacques Derrida.  aWalter Benjamin.  aanthropology.  aborder-as-process.  aborders.  aconflict.  amateriality.  amigration.  anationalism.  aphilosophy.  apolitical anthropology.  apolitical ideology.  apolity borders border-ness.  asouthern Europe.  astate apparatus.  astate borders.  atrace.1 aDe Cesari, Chiara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDemetriou, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDemetriou, Olga, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDimova, Rozita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDimova, Rozita, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGreen, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJansen, Stef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMyrivili, Eleni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPulkkinen, Tuija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612591040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526125910423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526125910/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles